org.wisepersist.gwt.uploader.client.events

Class FileDialogStartEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wisepersist.gwt.uploader.client.events.FileDialogStartEvent

  • public class FileDialogStartEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides access to the raw information provided by Uploader when a 'fileDialogStart' event occurs. This class should not be instantiated directly, but instead you should create a FileDialogStartHandler and register it via the .Uploader#setFileDialogStartHandler(FileDialogStartHandler) method in order to access file dialog start events.

    Note that the 'fileDialogStart' is fired after selectFile for selectFiles is called. This event is fired immediately before the File Selection Dialog window is displayed. However, the event may not execute until after the Dialog window is closed.
